    <custom_item>
      type        : FILE_CONTENT_CHECK
      description : "PHTN-30-000004 - The Photon operating system must limit the number of concurrent sessions to 10 for all accounts and/or account types."
      info        : "Operating system management includes the ability to control the number of users and user sessions that utilize an operating system. Limiting the number of allowed users and sessions per user is helpful in reducing the risks related to denial-of-service attacks."
      solution    : "At the command line, run the following command:

# echo '*       hard    maxlogins       10' >> /etc/security/limits.conf"
      reference   : "800-53|AC-10,800-53r5|AC-10,CAT|II,CCI|CCI-000054,CSF2.0|PR.AA-05,DISA_Benchmark|VMW_vSphere_7-0_vCA_Photon_OS_STIG,GDPR|32.1.b,HIPAA|164.306(a)(1),ITSG-33|AC-10,NESA|T5.5.1,QCSC-v1|5.2.1,QCSC-v1|5.2.2,Rule-ID|SV-256481r958398_rule,STIG-ID|PHTN-30-000004,Vuln-ID|V-256481"
